# MMS Auth & Users

## Stored user (canonical)

```ts
interface StoredUser {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  name: string;
  role: string;          // singular — NOT roles[]
  passwordHash: string;  // scrypt "salt:hash" hex
  createdAt: string;
}
```

JWT / API public shape: `User` from `@mms/shared` — `{ id, email, name, role }`.

## Seeds & UI alignment

- Seeds must include `passwordHash` and `role`. `roles: ['admin']` without hash **breaks login and onboarding**.
- UI fields for 2FA, `status`, `roles[]` in seeds are **display-only** until backend enforces them.

## Endpoints

| Route | Auth | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `POST /api/auth/login` | Public | Returns JWT |
| `POST /api/auth/onboard` | Public | First admin only → 409 if admin exists |
| `GET /api/auth/me` | JWT | Current user |
| `POST /api/auth/logout` | — | Client discards token (stateless JWT) |

`JWT_SECRET` required at startup.

## RBAC

Enforcement rules → **`mms-rbac.mdc`** (`rbacService`, `can()` hook target, registry `permissions`).

JWT / login shape only in this file — do not duplicate collection write matrices here.

## Session storage (current vs target)

| Approach | Status | Notes |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Bearer JWT in `localStorage` | **Current** | Simple SPA; vulnerable to XSS token theft — mitigate XSS strictly (`mms-security.mdc`) |
| httpOnly cookie + refresh | **Target** | Prefer for production hardening; requires CSRF strategy if cookie-based |

Until migration: never log token; clear on logout; treat XSS in rich text fields as security bugs.

## Frontend

- Token in `localStorage`; `AuthProvider` at app root
- **Single guard set** in `components/routing/`: `GuestRoute`, `ProtectedRoute`, `TenantGate`, `HostRoutes` — `ProtectedRoute.tsx` is canonical and used by `HostRoutes`
- Do **not** add a second auth wrapper in `App.tsx`, module pages, or layouts; remove duplicate imports when editing `App.tsx` (`mms-frontend.mdc`)
- Never log token or password values

## Password handling

- Hash/verify only in `userService` (scrypt + `timingSafeEqual`)
- Never send or store plaintext passwords outside the login/onboard request handler
